Cape Town - Two children were killed and two others injured in a fire in Fisantekraal in the early hours of Monday morning.City Fire Rescue teams were deployed to a fire in Goedverwagte Street just after midnight.Fire rescue spokesman Theo Layne said two children were killed, and two other children and an adult female sustained burn wounds.&#x201C;The fire broke out in one structure; it then spread and destroyed four structures, leaving 15 people displaced. The cause of the fire is undetermined,&#x201D; Layne said. Cape Argus IOL News on Facebook IOL on Twitter